article.description: UC Irvine beats UC Riverside 63-54 in Big West tourney
article.headline: UC Irvine beats UC Riverside 63-54 in Big West tourney
article.linkText: UC Irvine beats UC Riverside 63-54 in Big West tourney
article.story: ANAHEIM, Calif. -- Will Davis II had 17 points and 10 rebounds to lead No. 3 seed UC Irvine to a 63-54 victory over sixth-seeded UC Riverside in a Big West tournament quarterfinal on Thursday night. UC Irvine (19-12) will face either No. 2 seed UC Santa Barbara or seventh-seeded Cal Ply in a semifinal game on Friday. UC Riverside led 48-45 with 7:35 to play but UC Irvine answered with a 12-1 run to take a 57-49 lead with 1:58 left. The Highlanders pulled within 57-54, but the Anteaters hit 6 of 6 free throws to seal it. Davis was 8 of 10 from the floor and Luke Nelson chipped in 14 points with four assists for the Anteaters, who outrebounded the Highlanders 44-37. Taylor Johns scored 15 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead UC Riverside (14-17).
